Nick Wass Rain at Dover washes out qualifying; Kenseth on pole 
Crew members push the race car of Denny Hamlin in the garage area for the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race, Friday, Oct. 2, 2015, at Dover International Speedway in Dover, Del. (AP Photo/Nick Wass) Nick Wass Rain at Dover washes out qualifying; Kenseth on pole 
Team members load Danica Patrick's car back into the hauler in the garage area for the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race, Friday, Oct. 2, 2015, at Dover International Speedway in Dover, Del. (AP Photo/Nick Wass) Nick Wass Rain at Dover washes out qualifying; Kenseth on pole 
Rain beads up on a tire in the garage area for the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race, Friday, Oct. 2, 2015, at Dover International Speedway in Dover, Del. (AP Photo/Nick Wass) Nick Wass Rain at Dover washes out qualifying; Kenseth on pole 
Jeff Gordon speaks at an interview session for the NASCAR Sprint Cup series auto race, Friday, Oct. 2, 2015, at Dover International Speedway in Dover, Del. Gordon also received several gifts and awards including numerous Miles the Monster statues for him and his team. (AP Photo/Nick Wass) Posted: Friday, October 2, 2015 2:25 pm | Updated: 3:01 pm, Fri Oct 2, 2015. 
DOVER, Del. (AP) — For a driver on the brink of championship elimination, Kevin Harvick might have the biggest target at Dover.
